reviewText:
Sadly I found out that Dennis Eichhorn (who is in this film) died on October 8, 2015;

http://www.thestranger.com/blogs/slog/2015/10/09/22985836/sad-stuff-underground-comics-giant-dennis-eichhorn-is-dead
This is the story of a mentally ill but brilliant man who appeared with Frank Zappa.  we bought the CD after seeing it and there are interesting songs.  The story is well done and heartbreaking.

Somehow I never heard of this Wild Man Fischer before. Nevertheless I can see the attraction that he had on Great Artists like Frank Zappa. After seeing the dvd one time his songs remained in my head like glue.
Great documentary about a strange and also very lonely guy in the music bussiness.
I always thought "Wildman" was just an act.  This provocative documentary shows that Larry was truly crazy. Worth viewing even if you never heard of Wildman Fischer.
